  "text": "Substantial work has already been done in evaluating the success of the UK privatisation programme for electricity generation and transmission, notably by [CITATION_1] . These authors find that the net benefits of privatisation of the Central Electricity Generating Board in England and Wales, including the effect of changing fuel mix on meeting environmental objectives, were significantly positive. Nevertheless, the final impact of electricity privatisation on consumers must equally reflect the consequences of regulatory incentives and network utility responses to these, since about 40 per cent of the final supply price of electricity arises in the regulated sectors of distribution and transmission.",
